h5 Theme color palette description:

ul
	li "<strong>Base</strong>" color is used as <em>website background</em> color.

	li "<strong>Contrast</strong>" color is used as global <em>text color</em>. Set this for an appropriate contrast against "Base" color.

	li "<strong>Contrast alternative</strong>" color is used for <em>headings</em>. Set this for an appropriate contrast against "Base" color.

	li "<strong>Primary</strong>" color is an accent color <em>used on links</em>. Set this for an appropriate contrast against "Base" color.

	li "<strong>Primary mixed</strong>" color is subtle or contrasting version of "Primary" color. By default it was set as a blend of "Base" and "Primary" color. Not used by the theme, but helpful as subtle background for various sections and elements.

	li "<strong>Secondary</strong>" color is an accent color <em>used on buttons</em>. Set this to your liking.

	li "<strong>Secondary mixed</strong>" color is subtle or contrasting version of "Secondary" color. By default it was set as a blend of "Base" and "Secondary" color. Not used by the theme, but helpful as subtle background for various sections and elements.

+important( 'Gradients' )
	p Modifying theme palette colors also causes automatic recalculation of predefined gradients. This is done in background <em>after saving your color modifications and refreshing your browser window</em> (or visiting your website front-end).
	p If you don't want the recalculated gradients, feel free to modify gradients palette to your needs clicking the "Gradient" tab.
